         <abstract>
            <p>If accounting data are to perform a useful role in security analysis, they must be comparable across firms. Unfortunately, when firms buy the same asset at different times, or depreciate it differently, comparisons of profit performance are undermined and, with them, meaningful comparisons of internal goodwill.</p>
          </abstract>
